The theme underpinning the Tiny Project is … love. That may sound strange. But love is the force and energy that connects us all. And is what matters most. The question is: what do you love? Do you know? Do you spend some of your time each day doing things you love? Or do you get sidetracked? I do! How can we shift the balance? By taking tiny steps to add more of what we love to our lives.  
  
I find it helpful to make lists. Write down a piece of music or song that inspires or energises me. A film I want to watch. A tree that fills me with joy when I see it.  
  
I keep a daily log of small moments. I remember a flock of geese that flew overhead. The Goldfinches who come for breakfast around 09:30 each day.  
  
You can use a notebook or app. I love [@twosapp](https://www.instagram.com/twosapp/) - my favourite tool for writing things down.  
  
Then, when you have a few moments, you can check your list of loves and enjoy something from that list.  
  
What do you love? Choose a thing from your list today.

“The most valuable real estate in the world is the graveyard. There lie millions of half-written books, ideas never launched, and talents never developed. Most people die with everything still inside of them. The way to live is to create. Die empty. Get every idea out of your head and into reality. Calling yourself creative doesn’t make it true. Make finishing your top priority.” ~ Derek Sivers, How to Live 

This is the quote that kickstarted the Tiny Project. I want to get to the end of 2023 having created as much as I can, to give free rein to those ideas lurking inside my head, to launch, to publish, to share. 

But, mindful of all the other demands and responsibilities in our lives, this project is about tiny launches, tiny creations, tiny steps towards our goals. 

If this quote speaks to you, print it out, save it on your phone, and let it inspire you to create.
